Metadata Visualization Report

Visualization for group: subject:R AND domain:IAI AND skill:COQ AND subskill:QNT

1. Metadata Visualization

This plot is generated by retrieving vector embeddings from the Qdrant database and filtering the data purely based on metadata fields. The exact filters used are reflected in the section title above. The high-dimensional vectors were reduced to 2D using t-SNE to visualize how items cluster based on their metadata and label-wise difficulty.

2. KMeans Clustering with Elbow Method

Using the same metadata-filtered dataset as above, KMeans clustering was applied to identify natural groupings within the data. The Elbow method is used to estimate the optimal number of clusters. This helps in understanding how well-defined the group structures are within the filtered metadata.

3. Semantic Clustering

This visualization showcases the clustering of items based on semantic similarity. Unlike the previous graphs which used raw metadata filters, this graph is based on semantic vector embeddings fetched using a natural language prompt through semantic search. It reflects how conceptually similar items are grouped when interpreted via the models understanding.

The plot layout is driven by metadata, but the color labels applied to each point are derived from semantic label values. This layered approach helps us visually distinguish semantic groupings even within metadata-based spatial arrangements.
